Right-wing normie "by God.. look at this degeneracy,,," type clickbaity engagement accounts always cuck out by trying to say something general about capitalism, the West, Europeans, modernity, anything "neutral", but here the person directly calls out leftists, shitlibtards, etc.

Like an account called "Restoring Tradition For Our Sons" or "Men Against Modernity" is fundamentally conceptually cucked, just a guy whining about  how the world sucks and moralziing. But calling it "Look At These Shitlibs" makes it inherently culture-warlike, polemic, attacking

I disagree. Dr. Peat's philosophy is antithetical to this treating one's body as a "wise idol" sort of New Age platitude. On the contrary, emphasis is on intentionality and consciously understanding biologic processes. He forced some patients to read entire physiology textbooks.

Soviet medicine understood that actually knowing how a substance works improves its acting on the organism. Also knowledge accumulates with time and is fluid, one must emphasize active learning, autonomy, progress, dynamics. I am going to enforce Peat-thought purism against all.

Talking about one's body as something separate enforces mind-body dualism, calling it a "doctor" enforces authoritarian structures and subjugates "explorative, inquisitive" free consciousness under precisely the lower, animal aspects of one's being, the early evolutionary states.
